metadata.name: 11st Diner
metadata.description:
Together, the primary colors of light — red, green and blue — make white.
The absence of light makes black.

Night chromatics is about night lights, in fact night colors. A visual dialogue with some object. How we see them and how lights and colors can provide us feelings. Everyone has his way to see colors.

It’s a color study. How we paint the darkness of our towns with powerful neon colors in an urge to be seen, we use vivid light colors to call your eyes. Shops, parking, restaurant, Cab... Drawing with light or drawing with colors, photography can do both.

In the purest sense of street photography, these photos were shot handled, wandering, walking through the night, and looking for lights.
